 times, and there are a dozen different factors that go into deciding what I will work on on any given day.<br /><br />Also, Wild Cards is editing (I have written for the series, and hope to do so again, but just now I am too busy), which requires a whole different mindset than writing.   ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 months ago","ctime":"March 7 2017, 06:34:39 UTC","parent":25816464,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Writer&#39;s Block","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1488868479,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/524688.html?thread=25818512#t25818512","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/524688.html?thread=25818512#t25818512","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/524688.html?thread=25818512#t25818512","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_3182942","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://plus.google.com/102693515203676642736","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25818512,"talkid":100853,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/524688.html?thread=25818512#t25818512","upictitle":"Itamar Widerker: pic#0","article":"I've been in a constant state of \"Wait, why are they not all over this\" for the last 8 years with Hollywood and Wild Cards. Considering how in superheroes are, and considering your stature in the current television world, I'd think everyone would be jumping on \"Superheroes by the Game of Thrones guy\".<br /><br />I personally was really hoping for a movie with Gregg Hartmann until the recent election. I even imagined Andy Serkis taking up the mantle, though it may require a younger actor. However, the sort of deft political satire of five months ago is no longer possible. I'd still love to see what Melinda will make of this (assuming your involvement is minimal, as you're implying).","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 months ago","ctime":"March 7 2017, 11:00:25 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"I&#39;m glad for the Wild Cards news","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://plus.google.com/102693515203676642736","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/google-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Itamar Widerker","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_3182942","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=76143562&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Itamar Widerker","ctime_ts":1488884425,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/126383206/78290745","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/524688.html?thread=25828496#t25828496","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/524688.html?thread=25828496#t25828496","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/524688.html?thread=25828496#t25828496","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_3774220","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://www.facebook.com/app_scoped_user_id/10155096316712785/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25828496,"talkid":100892,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/524688.html?thread=25828496#t25828496","upictitle":"Raz Greenberg: pic#126383206","article":"I really hope you can make the TV show happen this time around. <br />Just a thought - there's a list of unproduced scripts by you at the bibliography page on your website. Any chance we'll see any of them in print or on-line? Yes, \"Doorways\" made it to VHS (and here's hoping there'll be some digital release in the future), and got a comics adaptation, and you published the script on the Dreamsongs anthology, along with the \"Road Less Traveled\" script... but I would love to read (or even get a comics adaptation, \"Doorways\"-style) of the other stuff that's listed on that page as well. Because I thought that \"Doorways\" was just awesome on all formats - VHS, the printed script and the comics adaptation. ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 months ago","ctime":"March 8 2017, 18:11:59 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"The post about the never-made Wild Cards film was great","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://www.facebook.com/app_scoped_user_id/10155096316712785/","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Raz Greenberg","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_3774220","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=78290745&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Raz Greenberg","ctime_ts":1488996719,"tracked":0}]}